   <!--THIS TOPIC IS PART OF THE BESR REPO, DO NOT EDIT IT WITHOUT CONSULTING WITH DATA FLOW AREA TECHWRITERS!!!-->
   <conbody>
      <p>Below ESR services are managed with the <apiname>besr_cluster</apiname> and <apiname>besr_local</apiname> commands. The general structure of these commands is as follows:</p>
      <codeblock>besr_cluster [options] &lt;command> &lt;component></codeblock>
      <codeblock>besr_local [options] &lt;command> &lt;component></codeblock>
      <p>Details and available commands vary between components. For details, use the <apiname>--help</apiname> option, or check the component specific parts of the documentation.</p>
      <note id="note_N1004B_N1002A_N10001" type="note">For managing clusters, using the <apiname>besr_cluster</apiname> command is recommended. This also applies to clusters that consist of a single host.</note>
      <p>The <apiname>besr_cluster</apiname> command logs its activity, and creates configuration backups for every action. These backups are created under <apiname>/data/config_backup</apiname>.</p>
   </conbody>
</concept>